item.description:
&lt;p class=&#34;w-full text-white text-justify py-2 mt-4 px-4 overflow-auto break-words&#34;&gt;Masti Express is a 2011 Indian Hindi-language comedy film directed by Vikram Pradhan and starring Rajpal Yadav, Divya Dutta and Johny Lever.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&#34;w-full text-white text-justify py-2 mt-4 px-4 overflow-auto break-words&#34;&gt;The songs were composed by Chinar–Mahesh. Lyrics by Manoj Yadav.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&#34;w-full text-white text-justify py-2 mt-4 px-4 overflow-auto break-words&#34;&gt;Taran Adarsh of Bollywood Hungama wrote that &#34;Quite an interesting idea, I must add, but interesting ideas don&#39;t necessarily translate into fascinating cinematic experiences&#34;.[3] Komal Nahta of Koimoi wrote that &#34;On the whole, Masti Express is too dull to impress at the box-office&#34;.[4] A critic from The Times of India wrote that &#34;Funny only in bits and pieces, Masti Express doesn&#39;t live up to its name&#34;.[5] A critic from Webdunia rated the film 2 out of 5.[6] A critic from Movie Talkies wrote that &#34;Unfortunately, the report card for Vikram Pradhan’s directorial debut reads ‘FAIL’. Ultimately, ‘Masti Express’ is a film thoroughly derailed&#34;.[7]&lt;/p&gt;

